Package: cloudberryos
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, python3 (>= 3.10), squid, nftables, adduser, sudo, libglib2.0-bin, dbus, xdg-utils
Suggests: gcompris-qt, tuxpaint, tuxmath, tuxtype, kiwix, libreoffice-writer, gimp, shotwell, hydrogen, lmms, audacity, godot3
Description: curated, filtered Ubuntu overlay for a child account
 CloudberryOS turns a stock Ubuntu install into a curated computing
 environment for a child: a local curated homepage, an allowlist proxy,
 per-child nftables firewall rules, and GNOME desktop polish.
 .
 Run "sudo cloudberryos-setup" after installing to create or configure the
 child account. Optional creative and educational app packs are offered by
 the setup wizard rather than being pulled in automatically.
